a-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-22_"><p class="sc-bfhwqR jqvVoJ pf-23_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmzxHC hSXinz pf-25_">Image by yanishevskaanna&nbsp;via Envato Elements</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-97a6" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dJjagV cQqdEF pf-26_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kCMLfs khbiTF"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-27_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-28_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-29_">Sowing resilience for a hunger-free future</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-31_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a6ad1452-09d1-451e-ae88-207d0d648d96"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Observed annually on 28 May, World Hunger Day shines a spotlight on the persistent issue of global hunger and food insecurity. Led by The Hunger Project, this initiative seeks to raise awareness about the root causes of hunger and inspire long-term, community-led solutions. The 2025 theme, “<em>Sowing Resilience</em>”, emphasises the urgent need to empower communities, fortify local food systems, and equip vulnerable populations to adapt and thrive in the face of adversity.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c835ea67-f89e-4d12-b766-13fac9311f14"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At The Mandatory Training Group, we stand united with this global movement. Through our expert-led training programmes and our compliance platform ComplyPlus™, we support organisations and communities in cultivating sustainable change and working toward a world where hunger is a challenge of the past.
<br>
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-39_">Understanding the scope of global hunger
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-41_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-1eae8820-7d0d-448d-9642-4a6bbd13b7ec"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Over 800 million people around the world continue to experience chronic hunger. Yet hunger is not just about food scarcity; it is a complex, multidimensional issue driven by factors such as poverty, inequality, conflict, climate change, lack of education, and gender disparity.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-44_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-fe3958b7-c6e7-47fd-87e9-6ed0e70f224f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Hunger disproportionately affects communities with limited access to resources, especially in developing regions. Tackling it requires more than temporary aid; it demands resilience-building strategies that promote long-term, sustainable change from within communities.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-47_">“<em>Sowing Resilience</em>” - More than just a metaphor
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-49_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-36a303f9-f151-4423-b3d4-7bdc255a02b3"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The 2025 theme, “<em>Sowing Resilience</em>”, speaks directly to the need to empower communities to develop lasting solutions to hunger. Resilience means more than bouncing back; it’s about preparing for future challenges, fostering self-reliance, and cultivating local knowledge and leadership.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-52_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4aabea82-8ef8-4b29-98c9-3adefc128306"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Resilient communities are those that:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eifsgl epDHtf pf-55_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-56_">Invest in climate-smart agriculture
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-58_">Empower women and marginalised groups
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-60_">Build local infrastructure and education systems
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-62_">Focus on sustainable livelihoods and food justice.
</li></ul><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-64_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-443fa648-ad84-47f1-8b32-5a965715d6a7"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Sowing resilience means planting the seeds today that will grow into robust, adaptable systems capable of withstanding tomorrow’s challenges.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-67_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-68_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-69_">Climate change and food security</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-71_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f96edf55-014c-4efe-8e84-0e19fede0328"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Climate change is a major threat to global food security. Unpredictable weather patterns, rising temperatures, and environmental degradation directly impact agricultural productivity, making it harder for communities to grow and access nutritious food.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-74_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-33cc5cd1-4a18-4796-a366-9c96b2679ef5"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">By promoting sustainable farming techniques, supporting ecological conservation, and empowering local farmers with the necessary skills and tools, we can build climate-resilient food systems that nourish communities and protect the planet.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-77_">Empowering women to lead the way
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-65f68788-96a9-48f3-b9c7-f0fc66be15e3"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Women are essential to the fight against hunger. In many developing countries, women are the primary food producers, yet they often face land ownership, education, and financial services barriers.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-82_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f80393b1-5835-4b72-b7fe-17dfe2d49d2f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">To truly sow resilience, we must prioritise gender equity by ensuring women have equal access to resources, training, and leadership opportunities. Empowering women means empowering entire communities, leading to healthier families, stronger economies, and more sustainable development.
<br>
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-85_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-86_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-87_">How to get involved in World Hunger Day 2025</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-89_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8e8f3b35-c7fd-47c8-8a52-4e6ae58a8cbd"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Everyone has a role to play in ending hunger and building resilience. Here are a few ways you can support this year’s theme:
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-92_">Educate and advocate</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-94_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8fa3b9e1-d8b7-45d1-87d8-f114bdcdab61"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Raise awareness about the root causes of hunger. Use social media to share resources, stories, and updates from organisations like The Hunger Project.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-97_">Support community-led solutions</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-99_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f114bdcd-ab61-4cc5-8263-f4632ed5cd62"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Donate to or partner with initiatives that empower local leaders and develop sustainable, long-term strategies.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-102_">Invest in ethical practices
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-104_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f4632ed5-cd62-4dc7-81ff-d6df3d28c721"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Choose to support businesses that uphold fair trade, environmental sustainability, and local sourcing.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-107_">Empower through training
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-109_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-d6df3d28-c721-480c-b5b2-5672d1554d3b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Invest in education and training, whether you’re part of a small business, nonprofit, or large organisation. Explore accredited courses through The Mandatory Training Group to drive meaningful change.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-112_">Leverage technology for impact
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-114_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5672d155-4d3b-483e-b604-1f0ae7314415"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Use tools like ComplyPlus™ to ensure your organisation meets sustainability goals, compliance requirements, and ethical governance standards.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-117_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-118_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-119_">Conclusion</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-121_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-1cd79b0e-3684-48d4-ad57-6a895c3fbd95"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">World Hunger Day 2025 is more than a campaign - it’s a call to action. The theme “<em>Sowing Resilience</em>” reminds us that ending hunger starts with building strength from within. Investing in education, supporting community leadership, and promoting sustainability can transform food systems and secure a future where no one goes hungry.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-124_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-75ef7044-e92a-4330-a4ce-eadbbc43f8e4"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Now, let’s plant the seeds for a more just, resilient, and hunger-free world.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-127_">The role of education, training and compliance
</h3><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-129_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8458d46d-576a-495c-bfbd-953ae78f5aa8"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Education and training are at the heart of sustainable development. At <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></em></a>, building resilient communities starts with equipping individuals and organisations with the knowledge, skills, and tools they need to lead lasting change.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-132_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cf99d08b-cb43-4828-8871-d9b2b3cdbd88"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Our work supports key targeted United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), including Zero Hunger (Goal 2), Quality Education (Goal 4), Gender Equality (Goal 5), and Climate Action (Goal 13).<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-135_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f3bd4d7c-c428-44b3-9ead-4c1a512d9fa6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Through our innovative compliance platform, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-regulatory-compliance-management-software" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">ComplyPlus™</span></em></a>, we help organisations:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eifsgl epDHtf pf-138_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-139_">Deliver accredited training in food safety, sustainability, and equality
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-141_">Develop inclusive, ethical governance frameworks
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-143_">Strengthen data-driven decision-making
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fKWLGC lflwGM pf-145_">Ensure compliance with global standards in humanitarian and development work.
</li></ul><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-147_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3477db2d-d88b-4213-9a56-666bdc035745"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">By aligning compliance, training, and development strategies, we contribute to the global effort to end hunger and build resilient systems that work for everyone.
</span></p><p class="sc-EROOM ZMPII pf-150_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-6d576a89-5c3f-4d95-bae7-8f5aa8664a2f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><em><strong>Last updated on 27-05-2025</strong></em></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-81b1" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dJjagV cQqdEF pf-153_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kCMLfs khbiTF"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-154_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-155_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gvZzpm chTUkt pf-156_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmzxHC hSXinz pf-158_">About the author
